Umbra Pax</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=marloon>Marloon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#333333>(12/3/02 11:44:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8043.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   hehe</span><hr size=1>  Yeah the Mage class rocks.  My first character was a cleric.  I probably would have stayed with that class except that 90 percent of all of eq are morons.  I love hearing &quot;The cleric is getting attacked! Run!&quot;  I made it 39 before I hated most every player in the game.  Then I made a mage just to mess around and he quickly became my favorate character.  I can group if I want to, or solo if I want to.  They are just all around fun to play.<br>
<br>
  I recently started a nerco alt just for fun.  I don't know a thing about nercos nor will I ever say I do. I just think it's fun that you can drop off some summoned items, plate and a staff to your nerco and give it to you skele pet at lvl 4+ and get 1 lvl every 5 to 10 min.  Yes, 5 to 10 min. lol.  I did that til lvl 7, then it became a little more time to level so I stopped playing.  If you want to have fun you should try it. it's great fun to see your xp bar actually move per kill.<br>
<br>
Marloon <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=variathemage>Varia the mage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#333333>(12/3/02 11:50:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8043.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why Mages Rock!!</span><hr size=1> I have a little 32 necro.  She rocked for soloing.  A decent bit easier to take blues and could take yellows and some reds while my mage had a hard time or couldn't do the same.  I have to agree though.  Fear kiting, while very powerful sub 60, is quite boring.  I'll probably eventually get her up to 50, but there is zero chance I'll ever change my main from a mage. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=108671">Varia Darselai</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> Arch Convoker</p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showPrevMessage?topicID=8043.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showNextMessage?topicID=8043.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8043.topic&index=7><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.threadControl?topicID=8043.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</